.TH mod_security 3 "inets 9.6.1" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
mod_security \- Security Audit and Trailing Functionality

.SH DESCRIPTION
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBblock_user(User, Address, Port, Dir, Seconds) ->\fR
\fB                    true | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        User :: string(),\fR
\fB                        Port :: inet:port_number(),\fR
\fB                        Address ::\fR
\fB                            inet:ip4_address() |\fR
\fB                            inet:ip6_address() |\fR
\fB                            string() |\fR
\fB                            undefined,\fR
\fB                        Dir :: string(),\fR
\fB                        Seconds :: non_neg_integer() | infinity,\fR
\fB                        Reason :: no_such_directory.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
\fIblock_user/4\fR and \fIblock_user/5\fR each blocks the user \fIUser\fR from directory \fIDir\fR for a specified amount of time.


.RE
.B
\fBlist_auth_users(Address, Port, Dir) -> Users | []\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Port :: inet:port_number(),\fR
\fB                             Address ::\fR
\fB                                 inet:ip4_address() |\fR
\fB                                 inet:ip6_address() |\fR
\fB                                 string() |\fR
\fB                                 undefined,\fR
\fB                             Dir :: string(),\fR
\fB                             Users :: [string()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
\fIlist_auth_users/1\fR, \fIlist_auth_users/2\fR, and \fIlist_auth_users/3\fR each returns a list of users that are currently authenticated. Authentications are stored for \fISecurityAuthTimeout\fR seconds, and then discarded.


.RE
.B
\fBlist_blocked_users(Address, Port, Dir) -> Users | []\fR
\fB                            when\fR
\fB                                Port :: integer(),\fR
\fB                                Address ::\fR
\fB                                    inet:ip4_address() |\fR
\fB                                    inet:ip6_address() |\fR
\fB                                    string() |\fR
\fB                                    undefined,\fR
\fB                                Dir :: string(),\fR
\fB                                Users ::\fR
\fB                                    [{blocked_user,\fR
\fB                                      term(),\fR
\fB                                      term(),\fR
\fB                                      term(),\fR
\fB                                      term()}].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
\fIlist_blocked_users/1\fR, \fIlist_blocked_users/2\fR, and \fIlist_blocked_users/3\fR each returns a list of users that are currently blocked from access.


.RE
.B
\fBunblock_user(User, Address, Port, Dir) -> true | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          User :: string(),\fR
\fB                          Port :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          Address ::\fR
\fB                              inet:ip4_address() |\fR
\fB                              inet:ip6_address() |\fR
\fB                              string() |\fR
\fB                              undefined,\fR
\fB                          Dir :: string(),\fR
\fB                          Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
\fIunblock_user/2\fR, \fIunblock_user/3\fR, and \fIunblock_user/4\fR each removes the user \fIUser\fR from the list of blocked users for \fIPort\fR (and \fIDir\fR).


.RE
.SH CALLBACKS
.LP
.B
\fBevent(What, Address, Port, Dir, Data)\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
\fIevent/4\fR or \fIevent/5\fR is called whenever an event occurs in the \fImod_security\fR Erlang web server API module. (\fIevent/4\fR is called if \fIAddress\fR is undefined, otherwise \fIevent/5\fR. Argument \fIWhat\fR specifies the type of event that has occurred and is one of the following reasons:

auth_fail
.RS 2
A failed user authentication.


.RE

user_block
.RS 2
A user is being blocked from access.


.RE

user_unblock
.RS 2
A user is being removed from the block list.


.RE

.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRThe event \fIuser_unblock\fR is not triggered when a user is removed from the block list explicitly using the \fIunblock_user\fR function.



.RE
